Title: BTRC Radio Belarus FM
Description: Radio Belarus International is a part of the National State TV and Radio Company of the Republic of Belarus. Our call sign has been present in the international air since May 11, 1962. Originally our transmissions were aired in Belarusian only. In 1985 we began broadcasting in German, and in 1998 our radio produced its first programs in Russian and English languages. Since 2006 the radio has been broadcasting in Polish. In 2010 we launched programs in French and Spanish, and in 2012 - in Chinese.

Title: BTRC Channel Culture
Description: "Culture" radio channel preferred by listeners interested in national and international cultural treasures and current events in art world.  The channel started its broadcasting on January, 1, 2002 and in short stood out among all other radio stations. Its motto is "We Stand for Immortal Treasures". You can enjoy opera, concerts of academic music, radio performances here, be a part of the discussions of the famous creative persons. There is also the "Mary Poppins" daily channel for the kids and multiple daily projects for the music amateurs the "Concert Hall" and the "Musical Europe" that do broadcast the concerts world over.
